{
    "Implementation approach": "We will use Flask as the REST framework, SQLAlchemy as the ORM with SQLite/PostgreSQL, Flask-Migrate for database migrations, and Flask-RESTful for structured API endpoints. Atomic transactions are guaranteed by wrapping withdrawal operations in database transactions with proper commit/rollback. Fraud detection will use rule-based heuristics (e.g., rapid successive withdrawals, amounts near daily limit, unusual hour patterns). Admin console endpoints are protected by role-based access. Audit logging is implemented via a dedicated model with timestamps. All libraries are open-source and widely adopted.",
    "File list": [
        "main.py",
        "config.py",
        "models.py",
        "services/__init__.py",
        "services/auth_service.py",
        "services/transaction_service.py",
        "services/fraud_service.py",
        "services/audit_service.py",
        "services/admin_service.py",
        "api/__init__.py",
        "api/auth_api.py",
        "api/transaction_api.py",
        "api/admin_api.py",
        "utils.py"
    ],
    "Data structures and interfaces": "\nclassDiagram\n    class User {\n        -int id\n        -string card_number\n        -string pin_hash\n        -string account_number\n        -float balance\n        -float daily_limit\n        -float daily_withdrawn_today\n        -date last_withdrawal_date\n        -bool is_locked\n        -int failed_attempts\n        +check_pin(pin: str) bool\n        +increment_failed_attempts()\n        +reset_failed_attempts()\n        +lock_account()\n        +unlock_account()\n    }\n    \n    class Transaction {\n        -int id\n        -int user_id\n        -float amount\n        -datetime timestamp\n        -string status  # pending, approved, declined, flagged\n        -string decline_reason\n        -bool is_flagged\n        +set_status(status: str)\n        +flag()\n    }\n    \n    class AuthenticationAttempt {\n        -int id\n        -int user_id\n        -datetime timestamp\n        -bool success\n        -string ip_address\n    }\n    \n    class AuditLog {\n        -int id\n        -string action\n        -int user_id\n        -int transaction_id\n        -string details\n        -datetime timestamp\n    }\n    \n    class FlaggedTransaction {\n        -int id\n        -int transaction_id\n        -string reason\n        -string severity  # low, medium, high\n        -int reviewed_by\n        -string review_status\n        -datetime review_timestamp\n    }\n    \n    class AuthService {\n        +authenticate(card_number: str, pin: str) User\n        +lock_account(user_id: int)\n        +unlock_account(user_id: int)\n        +get_failed_attempts(user_id: int) int\n    }\n    \n    class TransactionService {\n        -db_session\n        +process_withdrawal(user: User, amount: float) dict\n        +check_balance_and_limit(user: User, amount: float) bool\n        +execute_withdrawal(user: User, amount: float) Transaction\n        -rollback(transaction: Transaction)\n    }\n    \n    class FraudDetectionService {\n        +analyze_transaction(user: User, transaction: Transaction) bool\n        +flag_transaction(transaction: Transaction, reason: str)\n        +get_flagged_transactions() list[FlaggedTransaction]\n    }\n    \n    class AuditService {\n        +log_action(action: str, user_id: int, transaction_id: int, details: str)\n        +get_audit_logs(filters: dict) list[AuditLog]\n    }\n    \n    class AdminService {\n        +review_flagged_transaction(flagged_id: int, reviewer_id: int, status: str)\n        +lock_unlock_account(user_id: int, lock: bool)\n        +get_transaction_history(user_id: int) list[Transaction]\n        +get_audit_logs_history(filters: dict) list[AuditLog]\n    }\n    \n    User --> Transaction : has many\n    User --> AuthenticationAttempt : has many\n    Transaction --> FlaggedTransaction : can be flagged\n    AuthService --> User\n    TransactionService --> User\n    TransactionService --> Transaction\n    FraudDetectionService --> Transaction\n    FraudDetectionService --> FlaggedTransaction\n    AuditService --> AuditLog\n    AdminService --> User\n    AdminService --> FlaggedTransaction\n    AdminService --> Transaction\n    AdminService --> AuditLog\n",
    "Program call flow": "\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant ATM as ATM Terminal\n    participant API as Flask API\n    participant Auth as AuthService\n    participant UserDB as User Model\n    participant Tx as TransactionService\n    participant Audit as AuditService\n    participant Fraud as FraudDetectionService\n    participant DB as Database\n    participant Admin as Admin API\n\n    Note over ATM,API: Authentication Flow\n    ATM->>API: POST /auth/login (card_number, pin)\n    API->>Auth: authenticate(card_number, pin)\n    Auth->>UserDB: get user by card_number\n    alt User not found or locked\n        Auth-->>API: error response\n        API-->>ATM: 401 Unauthorized\n    else PIN correct\n        Auth->>UserDB: reset_failed_attempts()\n        Auth-->>API: success, return token\n        Auth->>Audit: log_action('LOGIN_SUCCESS', user_id, None, ...)\n        API-->>ATM: 200 OK, token\n    else PIN incorrect\n        Auth->>UserDB: increment_failed_attempts()\n        Auth->>Audit: log_action('LOGIN_FAILED', user_id, None, ...)\n        alt Failed attempts >= 3\n            Auth->>UserDB: lock_account()\n            Auth->>Audit: log_action('ACCOUNT_LOCKED', user_id, None, ...)\n            API-->>ATM: 423 Locked\n        else\n            API-->>ATM: 401 Unauthorized\n        end\n    end\n\n    Note over ATM,API: Withdrawal Flow\n    ATM->>API: POST /withdraw (amount, token)\n    API->>Auth: verify token\n    API->>Tx: process_withdrawal(user, amount)\n    Tx->>UserDB: get user (with balance, daily_limit, daily_withdrawn_today)\n    Tx->>Tx: check_balance_and_limit(user, amount)\n    alt Insufficient funds or exceeds daily limit\n        Tx-->>API: decline, reason\n        Tx->>Audit: log_action('WITHDRAWAL_DECLINED', user_id, None, reason)\n        API-->>ATM: 400 Bad Request, reason\n    else Valid\n        Tx->>DB: begin transaction\n        Tx->>UserDB: update balance and daily_withdrawn_today\n        Tx->>UserDB: create Transaction record (pending)\n        Tx->>Fraud: analyze_transaction(user, transaction)\n        alt Suspicious\n            Fraud->>Fraud: flag_transaction(transaction, reason)\n            Fraud->>Tx: mark transaction as flagged\n        end\n        Tx->>UserDB: set transaction status to 'approved'\n        Tx->>DB: commit\n        Tx-->>API: success, transaction_id\n        Tx->>Audit: log_action('WITHDRAWAL_SUCCESS', user_id, transaction.id, amount)\n        API-->>ATM: 200 OK, transaction_id\n        note over Tx: If any failure during DB update, rollback\n    end\n\n    Note over Admin,API: Admin Review\n    Admin->>API: GET /admin/flagged\n    API->>Fraud: get_flagged_transactions()\n    Fraud-->>API: list of flagged transactions\n    API-->>Admin: JSON response\n    Admin->>API: POST /admin/review (flagged_id, status)\n    API->>AdminService: review_flagged_transaction(...)\n    AdminService->>Audit: log_action('FLAGGED_REVIEWED', reviewer_id, transaction_id, status)\n    API-->>Admin: 200 OK\n    Admin->>API: POST /admin/account/lock (user_id, lock=true)\n    API->>AdminService: lock_unlock_account(user_id, lock)\n    AdminService->>UserDB: lock/unlock account\n    AdminService->>Audit: log_action('ACCOUNT_LOCK_STATUS_CHANGED', user_id, None, lock_status)\n    API-->>Admin: 200 OK\n",
    "Anything UNCLEAR": "The definition of 'suspicious withdrawal patterns' needs clarification. The current design uses rule-based heuristics (rapid successive withdrawals, amounts near daily limit, times outside usual hours). If machine learning or more complex detection is required, the FraudDetectionService can be extended later. Additionally, the integration protocol with physical ATM terminals is not specified; we assume RESTful HTTPS with token-based authentication for ATMs."
}
[/CONTENT]
